      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "JAKE'S DESIRE (8) goes very well this course and distance starting 14 times for seven wins and two minors. Comes off a (18.74) win last time, scoring by a nose in a NG over 330m at this track. Looks the one to beat with even luck. LET'S GO OUT (5) failed to come into contention last start at this track, but prior to that won by a nose at this track (18.72) beating PIGEON'S DESIRE in a Grade 3/4 on June 10. Solid beginner who can clear the tricky draw. Can measure up this time. TIGGERLONG BINGO (2) was strongly fancied latest and proved too good with a 1.5 lengths win at Wagga in a handy 18.05. Draws to advantage and has a good record over this journey. Form from his last run is proving strong. Leading player again. PIGEON'S DESIRE (4) is another with top-three prospects.",
